Salty or regarding salt content (quoted from http://www.fishbase.org/Glossary/Glossary.cfm?TermEnglish=haline). Used for example as part of the compound word thermohaline, regarding temperature and salinity, which in turn is most commonly used in the phrase "thermohaline circulation" which is an ocean current caused by temperature and salinity differences between masses of water. It would be nice if the term "saline" was simply used instead.